## ‚ùå Common Mistakes to Avoid

### Backend
- ‚ùå Don't expose MongoDB _id directly (use virtual 'id')
- ‚ùå Don't return passwords in API responses
- ‚ùå Don't use try-catch without proper error handling
- ‚ùå Don't forget to validate inputs
- ‚ùå Don't use any type in TypeScript

### Frontend
- ‚ùå Don't use useEffect for data fetching
- ‚ùå Don't store tokens in localStorage
- ‚ùå Don't forget loading and error states
- ‚ùå Don't prop drill (use context or Zustand)
- ‚ùå Don't mutate state directly

